        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 2:33PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 233 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles northwest of McKeever, or 14 miles north of Boonville, moving
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Big Moose, McKeever, Moshier Falls, Nicks Lake Campground, Old Forge,
Minnehaha, Thendara, Carter Station, Mountain Lodge, Lyon Lake, Alger
Island Public Campground, and Woods Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
eastern New York.</instruction>
